Recommendations

* Operating Systems

  SyMBA can be installed on either Windows or Linux, but we highly recommend a
  Linux system, specifically Ubuntu.

  If you use Ubuntu, it is simple to apt-get the components required. Alternatively, you could create a Virtual
  Machine and install the latest Ubuntu Server (or Standard) release on it. Ubuntu has the
  advantage that it has PostgreSQL and Maven 2.x in its package repository. During the Ubuntu server installation it
  even asks whether you want to install a database server.

